cluster_name.description: Name by which this cluster will be known as.

config_git_url.description: URL to the Magic Castle Puppet configuration git repo

config_version.description: Tag, branch, or commit that specifies which Puppet configuration revision is to be used

domain.description: String which when combined with cluster_name will formed the cluster FQDN

firewall_rules.description: List of login external firewall rules defined as map of 5 values name, from_port, to_port, ip_protocol and cidr

generate_ssh_key.description: If set to true, Terraform will generate an ssh key pair to connect to the cluster. Default: false

guest_passwd.description: Guest accounts common password. If left blank, the password is randomly generated.

hieradata.description: String formatted as YAML defining hiera key-value pairs to be included in the puppet environment

image.description: Name of the operating system image that will be used to create a boot disk for the instances

instances.description: Map that defines the parameters for each type of instance of the cluster

nb_users.description: Number of user accounts with a common password that will be created

public_keys.description: List of SSH public keys that can log in as {sudoer_username}

software_stack.description: Provider of research computing software stack (can be 'computecanada' or 'eessi')

volumes.description: Map that defines the volumes to be attached to the instances
